sub_title: Project Engineering Management / Business and Technology
summary:
Experience in Lean Six Sigma with understanding Theory of Constraints through analysis of business case studies. Practiced business process management fundamentals and supply chain management tools and techniques. My business principles and leadership skills include: 

-Project planning and design / Project management
-Business process management notation and systems process improvement
-ERP systems
-Change management
-Risk Management 

Knowledge of Electrical Power Systems and software, interpretation of Electrical, Civil, Structural engineering drawings through Electrical Power Engineering courses. Completed Communication Skills for Engineering course (CCDP 2100): emphasized on communication, group work, oral presentations, and technical writing. Engineering technical skills include: 

-Circuit design, Simulation, Construction and testing
-Wireless technology, Hardware/Software Interfacing
-FPGA expertise (Altera & Xilinx)
-Image processing (MATLAB / AUTOCAD)
-Electronic theory and principals

I have practiced in diverse and challenging work environments, gaining extensive experience and perfecting my communication skills.
